nd its features into a Docker image, build the Docker image, run it as a container, and then test the deployed API."]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"a29d678c"},"source":["## Create Dockerfile\n","\n","### Subtask:\n","Generate a Dockerfile that specifies the environment for the Flask application. This includes selecting a base image, installing Python dependencies (Flask, pandas, scikit-learn, joblib), copying the app.py script, random_forest_model.joblib, and model_features.joblib into the image, exposing the port, and defining the command to run the Flask application.\n"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"a158e223"},"source":["**Reasoning**:\n","To prepare for the Dockerfile creation, I need to save the trained `RandomForestRegressor` model and the list of feature columns (`X_train.columns`) to disk using `joblib`. These files (`random_forest_model.joblib` and `model_features.joblib`) will then be included in the Docker image.\n","\n"]},{"cell_type":"code","metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"a10804db","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1772554176741,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":128,"user":{"displayName":"RAKESH DHANORIYA","userId":"02116516191574127798"}},"outputId":"b7f6cee9-d0f9-4e42-c0f1-53bc9668a010"},"source":["import joblib\n","\n","# Define filenames for the model and feature columns\n","model_filename = 'random_forest_model.joblib'\n","features_filename = 'model_features.joblib'\n","\n","# Save the trained model\n","joblib.dump(model, model_filename)\n","print(f\"Trained model saved as {model_filename}\")\n","\n","# Save the list of feature columns (in the correct order)\n","model_features = X_train.columns.tolist()\n","joblib.dump(model_features, features_filename)\n","print(f\"Model features saved as {features_filename}\")\n","\n","print(\"Model and features saved successfully.\")"],"execution_count":16,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Trained model saved as random_forest_model.joblib\n","Model features saved as model_features.joblib\n","Model and features saved successfully.\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"fe80ddc5"},"source":["**Reasoning**:\n","As instructed, I will create the `app.py` file containing the Flask application logic. This script will load the saved model and features, define a `/predict` endpoint, and use the model to make predictions based on incoming JSON data.\n","\n"]},{"cell_type":"code","metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"5d9f1143","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1772554183899,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":18,"user":{"displayName":"RAKESH DHANORIYA","userId":"02116516191574127798"}},"outputId":"e45e9e1a-87eb-478c-c827-6aa2ab90e6a4"},"source":["%%writefile app.py\n","\n","from flask import Flask, request, jsonify\n","import joblib\n","import pandas as pd\n","import numpy as np\n","\n","# Load the trained model and feature columns\n","model = joblib.load('random_forest_model.joblib')\n","model_features = joblib.load('model_features.joblib')\n","\n","app = Flask(__name__)\n","\n","@app.route('/predict', methods=['POST'])\n","def predict():\n","    try:\n","        json_ = request.json\n","        # Create a DataFrame from the incoming JSON data\n","        # Ensure the order of columns matches the training data\n","        query_df = pd.DataFrame(json_)\n","\n","        # Handle boolean columns explicitly if necessary (get_dummies converts to bool)\n","        for feature in model_features:\n","            if feature not in query_df.columns:\n","                query_df[feature] = False # Default to False if feature not present in query_df\n","\n","        # Ensure the order of columns matches model_features\n","        query_df = query_df[model_features]\n","\n","        prediction = model.predict(query_df)\n","\n","        return jsonify({'prediction': list(prediction)})\n","\n","    except Exception as e:\n","        return jsonify({'error': str(e)}), 400\n","\n","if __name__ == '__main__':\n","    app.run(host='0.0.0.0', port=5000)"],"execution_count":17,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Writing app.py\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"42a97934"},"source":["**Reasoning**:\n","To ensure the Docker image can correctly install all necessary Python dependencies, I need to create a `requirements.txt` file that lists them. This file will include `Flask`, `pandas`, and `scikit-learn`.\n","\n"]},{"cell_type":"code","metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"5b28021c","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1772554192421,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":160,"user":{"displayName":"RAKESH DHANORIYA","userId":"02116516191574127798"}},"outputId":"f2566f97-4bfd-4122-f2dc-9dae38a345c6"},"source":["%%writefile requirements.txt\n","Flask==2.3.2\n","pandas==1.5.3\n","scikit-learn==1.2.2\n","numpy==1.23.5\n","joblib==1.2.0\n"],"execution_count":18,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Writing requirements.txt\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"a0b215da"},"source":["**Reasoning**:\n","Now that the model, features, `app.py`, and `requirements.txt` are ready, I will create the `Dockerfile` to define the container environment for the Flask application as specified in the subtask.\n","\n"]},{"cell_type":"code","metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"c2cc7b6f","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1772554198834,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":20,"user":{"displayName":"RAKESH DHANORIYA","userId":"02116516191574127798"}},"outputId":"577b1585-80b0-48da-fa8f-53c3491e14ce"},"source":["%%writefile Dockerfile\n","\n","# Use an official Python runtime as a parent image\n","FROM python:3.9-slim-buster\n","\n","# Set the working directory in the container\n","WORKDIR /app\n","\n","# Copy the current directory contents into the container at /app\n","COPY . /app\n","\n","# Install any needed packages specified in requirements.txt\n","RUN pip install --no-cache-dir -r requirements.txt\n","\n","# Make port 5000 available to the world outside this container\n","EXPOSE 5000\n","\n","# Define environment variable\n","ENV FLASK_APP=app.py\n","\n","# Run app.py when the container launches\n","CMD [\"python\", \"app.py\"]"],"execution_count":19,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Writing Dockerfile\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"code","source":[],"metadata":{"id":"Qnap0kBvZ3Bd"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"9e2d2361"},"source":["## Build Docker Image\n","\n","### Subtask:\n","Provide instructions on how to build the Docker image using the Dockerfile. This will involve using the `docker build` command to create a runnable image that contains the model and API.\n"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"81d10d82"},"source":["To build the Docker image, open your terminal or command prompt and navigate to the directory where your `Dockerfile`, `app.py`, `requirements.txt`, `random_forest_model.joblib`, and `model_features.joblib` files are located. Then, execute the following command:\n","\n","```bash\n","docker build -t flight-price-predictor .\n","```\n","\n","This command will:\n","- `-t flight-price-predictor`: Tag the image with the name `flight-price-predictor`. You can choose any name you prefer.\n","- `.`:  Indicate that the Dockerfile is in the current directory."]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"1a0276b2"},"source":["\n"]},{"cell_type":"code","source":[],"metadata":{"id":"jaqudgGmdv8h"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"73ad390a"},"source":["\n"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"cc44020e"},"source":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"0b26716b"},"source":["## Test Deployed API\n","\n","### Subtask:\n","Provide instructions and example code (using curl or Python requests) to test the API running within the Docker container, similar to how the local Flask API was teste